article.description: James Baker Jr. had 14 points as Morehead State beat Southeast Missouri 64-50 on Saturday.
article.headline: Morehead State wins fifth straight game
article.linkText: Morehead State wins fifth straight game
article.story: James Baker Jr. had 14 points as Morehead State beat Southeast Missouri 64-50 on Saturday. Skyelar Potter had 11 points for Morehead State (9-6, 6-2 Ohio Valley Conference), which won its fifth straight game. De’Von Cooper added 11 points. Johni Broome had 10 points. Southeast Missouri totaled 19 points in the second half, a season low for the team. The game was tied at halftime. Nana Akenten had 14 points for the Redhawks (3-8, 1-4). Manny Patterson added three blocks. Chris Harris, the Redhawks’ leading scorer heading into the contest at 16.0 points per game, scored five points on 2-of-10 shooting. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
